 428 _HASH_RE = re.compile(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9./=]')

 431 class User(object):
 432     """
 433     This is a generic User manipulation class that is subclassed
 434     based on platform.
 435 
 436     A subclass may wish to override the following action methods:-
 437       - create_user()
 438       - remove_user()
 439       - modify_user()
 440       - ssh_key_gen()
 441       - ssh_key_fingerprint()
 442       - user_exists()
 443 
 444     All subclasses MUST define platform and distribution (which may be None).
 445     """
 446 
 447     platform = 'Generic'
 448     distribution = None
 449     PASSWORDFILE = '/etc/passwd'
 450     SHADOWFILE = '/etc/shadow'
 451     SHADOWFILE_EXPIRE_INDEX = 7
 452     LOGIN_DEFS = '/etc/login.defs'
 453     DATE_FORMAT = '%Y-%m-%d'
 454 
 455     def __new__(cls, *args, **kwargs):
 456         new_cls = get_platform_subclass(User)
 457         return super(cls, new_cls).__new__(new_cls)
 458 
 459     def __init__(self, module):
 460         self.module = module
 461         self.state = module.params['state']
 462         self.name = module.params['name']
 463         self.uid = module.params['uid']
 464         self.hidden = module.params['hidden']
 465         self.non_unique = module.params['non_unique']
 466         self.seuser = module.params['seuser']
 467         self.group = module.params['group']
 468         self.comment = module.params['comment']
 469         self.shell = module.params['shell']
 470         self.password = module.params['password']
 471         self.force = module.params['force']
 472         self.remove = module.params['remove']
 473         self.create_home = module.params['create_home']
 474         self.move_home = module.params['move_home']
 475         self.skeleton = module.params['skeleton']
 476         self.system = module.params['system']
 477         self.login_class = module.params['login_class']
 478         self.append = module.params['append']
 479         self.sshkeygen = module.params['generate_ssh_key']
 480         self.ssh_bits = module.params['ssh_key_bits']
 481         self.ssh_type = module.params['ssh_key_type']
 482         self.ssh_comment = module.params['ssh_key_comment']
 483         self.ssh_passphrase = module.params['ssh_key_passphrase']
 484         self.update_password = module.params['update_password']
 485         self.home = module.params['home']
 486         self.expires = None
 487         self.password_lock = module.params['password_lock']
 488         self.groups = None
 489         self.local = module.params['local']
 490         self.profile = module.params['profile']
 491         self.authorization = module.params['authorization']
 492         self.role = module.params['role']
 493 
 494         if module.params['groups'] is not None:
 495             self.groups = ','.join(module.params['groups'])
 496 
 497         if module.params['expires'] is not None:
 498             try:
 499                 self.expires = time.gmtime(module.params['expires'])
 500             except Exception as e:
 501                 module.fail_json(msg="Invalid value for 'expires' %s: %s" % (self.expires, to_native(e)))
 502 
 503         if module.params['ssh_key_file'] is not None:
 504             self.ssh_file = module.params['ssh_key_file']
 505         else:
 506             self.ssh_file = os.path.join('.ssh', 'id_%s' % self.ssh_type)
 507 
 508         if self.groups is None and self.append:
 509             # Change the argument_spec in 2.14 and remove this warning
 510             # required_by={'append': ['groups']}
 511             module.warn("'append' is set, but no 'groups' are specified. Use 'groups' for appending new groups."
 512                         "This will change to an error in Ansible 2.14.")
 513 
 514     def check_password_encrypted(self):
 515         # Darwin needs cleartext password, so skip validation
 516         if self.module.params['password'] and self.platform != 'Darwin':
 517             maybe_invalid = False
 518 
 519             # Allow setting certain passwords in order to disable the account
 520             if self.module.params['password'] in set(['*', '!', '*************']):
 521                 maybe_invalid = False
 522             else:
 523                 # : for delimiter, * for disable user, ! for lock user
 524                 # these characters are invalid in the password
 525                 if any(char in self.module.params['password'] for char in ':*!'):
 526                     maybe_invalid = True
 527                 if '$' not in self.module.params['password']:
 528                     maybe_invalid = True
 529                 else:
 530                     fields = self.module.params['password'].split("$")
 531                     if len(fields) >= 3:
 532                         # contains character outside the crypto constraint
 533                         if bool(_HASH_RE.search(fields[-1])):
 534                             maybe_invalid = True
 535                         # md5
 536                         if fields[1] == '1' and len(fields[-1]) != 22:
 537                             maybe_invalid = True
 538                         # sha256
 539                         if fields[1] == '5' and len(fields[-1]) != 43:
 540                             maybe_invalid = True
 541                         # sha512
 542                         if fields[1] == '6' and len(fields[-1]) != 86:
 543                             maybe_invalid = True
 544                     else:
 545                         maybe_invalid = True
 546             if maybe_invalid:
 547                 self.module.warn("The input password appears not to have been hashed. "
 548                                  "The 'password' argument must be encrypted for this module to work properly.")
 549 
 550     def execute_command(self, cmd, use_unsafe_shell=False, data=None, obey_checkmode=True):
 551         if self.module.check_mode and obey_checkmode:
 552             self.module.debug('In check mode, would have run: "%s"' % cmd)
 553             return (0, '', '')
 554         else:
 555             # cast all args to strings ansible-modules-core/issues/4397
 556             cmd = [str(x) for x in cmd]
 557             return self.module.run_command(cmd, use_unsafe_shell=use_unsafe_shell, data=data)
 558 
 559     def backup_shadow(self):
 560         if not self.module.check_mode and self.SHADOWFILE:
 561             return self.module.backup_local(self.SHADOWFILE)
 562 
 563     def remove_user_userdel(self):
 564         if self.local:
 565             command_name = 'luserdel'
 566         else:
 567             command_name = 'userdel'
 568 
 569         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path(command_name, True)]
 570         if self.force and not self.local:
 571             cmd.append('-f')
 572         if self.remove:
 573             cmd.append('-r')
 574         cmd.append(self.name)
 575 
 576         return self.execute_command(cmd)

 578     def create_user_useradd(self):
 579 
 580         if self.local:
 581             command_name = 'luseradd'
 582             lgroupmod_cmd = self.module.get_bin_path('lgroupmod', True)
 583         else:
 584             command_name = 'useradd'
 585 
 586         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path(command_name, True)]
 587 
 588         if self.uid is not None:
 589             cmd.append('-u')
 590             cmd.append(self.uid)
 591 
 592             if self.non_unique:
 593                 cmd.append('-o')
 594 
 595         if self.seuser is not None:
 596             cmd.append('-Z')
 597             cmd.append(self.seuser)
 598         if self.group is not None:
 599             if not self.group_exists(self.group):
 600                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % self.group)
 601             cmd.append('-g')
 602             cmd.append(self.group)
 603         elif self.group_exists(self.name):
 604             # use the -N option (no user group) if a group already
 605             # exists with the same name as the user to prevent
 606             # errors from useradd trying to create a group when
 607             # USERGROUPS_ENAB is set in /etc/login.defs.
 608             if os.path.exists('/etc/redhat-release'):
 609                 dist = distro.linux_distribution(full_distribution_name=False)
 610                 major_release = int(dist[1].split('.')[0])
 611                 if major_release <= 5 or self.local:
 612                     cmd.append('-n')
 613                 else:
 614                     cmd.append('-N')
 615             elif os.path.exists('/etc/SuSE-release'):
 616                 # -N did not exist in useradd before SLE 11 and did not
 617                 # automatically create a group
 618                 dist = distro.linux_distribution(full_distribution_name=False)
 619                 major_release = int(dist[1].split('.')[0])
 620                 if major_release >= 12:
 621                     cmd.append('-N')
 622             else:
 623                 cmd.append('-N')
 624 
 625         if self.groups is not None and len(self.groups):
 626             groups = self.get_groups_set()
 627             if not self.local:
 628                 cmd.append('-G')
 629                 cmd.append(','.join(groups))
 630 
 631         if self.comment is not None:
 632             cmd.append('-c')
 633             cmd.append(self.comment)
 634 
 635         if self.home is not None:
 636             # If the specified path to the user home contains parent directories that
 637             # do not exist, first create the home directory since useradd cannot
 638             # create parent directories
 639             parent = os.path.dirname(self.home)
 640             if not os.path.isdir(parent):
 641                 self.create_homedir(self.home)
 642             cmd.append('-d')
 643             cmd.append(self.home)
 644 
 645         if self.shell is not None:
 646             cmd.append('-s')
 647             cmd.append(self.shell)
 648 
 649         if self.expires is not None:
 650             cmd.append('-e')
 651             if self.expires < time.gmtime(0):
 652                 cmd.append('')
 653             else:
 654                 cmd.append(time.strftime(self.DATE_FORMAT, self.expires))
 655 
 656         if self.password is not None:
 657             cmd.append('-p')
 658             cmd.append(self.password)
 659 
 660         if self.create_home:
 661             if not self.local:
 662                 cmd.append('-m')
 663 
 664             if self.skeleton is not None:
 665                 cmd.append('-k')
 666                 cmd.append(self.skeleton)
 667         else:
 668             cmd.append('-M')
 669 
 670         if self.system:
 671             cmd.append('-r')
 672 
 673         cmd.append(self.name)
 674         (rc, err, out) = self.execute_command(cmd)
 675         if not self.local or rc != 0 or self.groups is None or len(self.groups) == 0:
 676             return (rc, err, out)
 677 
 678         for add_group in groups:
 679             (rc, _err, _out) = self.execute_command([lgroupmod_cmd, '-M', self.name, add_group])
 680             out += _out
 681             err += _err
 682             if rc != 0:
 683                 return (rc, out, err)
 684         return (rc, out, err)

 686     def _check_usermod_append(self):
 687         # check if this version of usermod can append groups
 688 
 689         if self.local:
 690             command_name = 'lusermod'
 691         else:
 692             command_name = 'usermod'
 693 
 694         usermod_path = self.module.get_bin_path(command_name, True)
 695 
 696         # for some reason, usermod --help cannot be used by non root
 697         # on RH/Fedora, due to lack of execute bit for others
 698         if not os.access(usermod_path, os.X_OK):
 699             return False
 700 
 701         cmd = [usermod_path, '--help']
 702         (rc, data1, data2) = self.execute_command(cmd, obey_checkmode=False)
 703         helpout = data1 + data2
 704 
 705         # check if --append exists
 706         lines = to_native(helpout).split('\n')
 707         for line in lines:
 708             if line.strip().startswith('-a, --append'):
 709                 return True
 710 
 711         return False

 713     def modify_user_usermod(self):
 714 
 715         if self.local:
 716             command_name = 'lusermod'
 717             lgroupmod_cmd = self.module.get_bin_path('lgroupmod', True)
 718             lgroupmod_add = set()
 719             lgroupmod_del = set()
 720         else:
 721             command_name = 'usermod'
 722 
 723         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path(command_name, True)]
 724         info = self.user_info()
 725         has_append = self._check_usermod_append()
 726 
 727         if self.uid is not None and info[2] != int(self.uid):
 728             cmd.append('-u')
 729             cmd.append(self.uid)
 730 
 731             if self.non_unique:
 732                 cmd.append('-o')
 733 
 734         if self.group is not None:
 735             if not self.group_exists(self.group):
 736                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % self.group)
 737             ginfo = self.group_info(self.group)
 738             if info[3] != ginfo[2]:
 739                 cmd.append('-g')
 740                 cmd.append(self.group)
 741 
 742         if self.groups is not None:
 743             # get a list of all groups for the user, including the primary
 744             current_groups = self.user_group_membership(exclude_primary=False)
 745             groups_need_mod = False
 746             groups = []
 747 
 748             if self.groups == '':
 749                 if current_groups and not self.append:
 750                     groups_need_mod = True
 751             else:
 752                 groups = self.get_groups_set(remove_existing=False)
 753                 group_diff = set(current_groups).symmetric_difference(groups)
 754 
 755                 if group_diff:
 756                     if self.append:
 757                         for g in groups:
 758                             if g in group_diff:
 759                                 if has_append:
 760                                     cmd.append('-a')
 761                                 groups_need_mod = True
 762                                 break
 763                     else:
 764                         groups_need_mod = True
 765 
 766             if groups_need_mod:
 767                 if self.local:
 768                     if self.append:
 769                         lgroupmod_add = set(groups).difference(current_groups)
 770                         lgroupmod_del = set()
 771                     else:
 772                         lgroupmod_add = set(groups).difference(current_groups)
 773                         lgroupmod_del = set(current_groups).difference(groups)
 774                 else:
 775                     if self.append and not has_append:
 776                         cmd.append('-A')
 777                         cmd.append(','.join(group_diff))
 778                     else:
 779                         cmd.append('-G')
 780                         cmd.append(','.join(groups))
 781 
 782         if self.comment is not None and info[4] != self.comment:
 783             cmd.append('-c')
 784             cmd.append(self.comment)
 785 
 786         if self.home is not None and info[5] != self.home:
 787             cmd.append('-d')
 788             cmd.append(self.home)
 789             if self.move_home:
 790                 cmd.append('-m')
 791 
 792         if self.shell is not None and info[6] != self.shell:
 793             cmd.append('-s')
 794             cmd.append(self.shell)
 795 
 796         if self.expires is not None:
 797 
 798             current_expires = int(self.user_password()[1])
 799 
 800             if self.expires < time.gmtime(0):
 801                 if current_expires >= 0:
 802                     cmd.append('-e')
 803                     cmd.append('')
 804             else:
 805                 # Convert days since Epoch to seconds since Epoch as struct_time
 806                 current_expire_date = time.gmtime(current_expires * 86400)
 807 
 808                 # Current expires is negative or we compare year, month, and day only
 809                 if current_expires < 0 or current_expire_date[:3] != self.expires[:3]:
 810                     cmd.append('-e')
 811                     cmd.append(time.strftime(self.DATE_FORMAT, self.expires))
 812 
 813         # Lock if no password or unlocked, unlock only if locked
 814         if self.password_lock and not info[1].startswith('!'):
 815             cmd.append('-L')
 816         elif self.password_lock is False and info[1].startswith('!'):
 817             # usermod will refuse to unlock a user with no password, module shows 'changed' regardless
 818             cmd.append('-U')
 819 
 820         if self.update_password == 'always' and self.password is not None and info[1] != self.password:
 821             cmd.append('-p')
 822             cmd.append(self.password)
 823 
 824         (rc, err, out) = (None, '', '')
 825 
 826         # skip if no usermod changes to be made
 827         if len(cmd) > 1:
 828             cmd.append(self.name)
 829             (rc, err, out) = self.execute_command(cmd)
 830 
 831         if not self.local or not (rc is None or rc == 0) or (len(lgroupmod_add) == 0 and len(lgroupmod_del) == 0):
 832             return (rc, err, out)
 833 
 834         for add_group in lgroupmod_add:
 835             (rc, _err, _out) = self.execute_command([lgroupmod_cmd, '-M', self.name, add_group])
 836             out += _out
 837             err += _err
 838             if rc != 0:
 839                 return (rc, out, err)
 840 
 841         for del_group in lgroupmod_del:
 842             (rc, _err, _out) = self.execute_command([lgroupmod_cmd, '-m', self.name, del_group])
 843             out += _out
 844             err += _err
 845             if rc != 0:
 846                 return (rc, out, err)
 847         return (rc, out, err)

 849     def group_exists(self, group):
 850         try:
 851             # Try group as a gid first
 852             grp.getgrgid(int(group))
 853             return True
 854         except (ValueError, KeyError):
 855             try:
 856                 grp.getgrnam(group)
 857                 return True
 858             except KeyError:
 859                 return False
 860 
 861     def group_info(self, group):
 862         if not self.group_exists(group):
 863             return False
 864         try:
 865             # Try group as a gid first
 866             return list(grp.getgrgid(int(group)))
 867         except (ValueError, KeyError):
 868             return list(grp.getgrnam(group))

 870     def get_groups_set(self, remove_existing=True):
 871         if self.groups is None:
 872             return None
 873         info = self.user_info()
 874         groups = set(x.strip() for x in self.groups.split(',') if x)
 875         for g in groups.copy():
 876             if not self.group_exists(g):
 877                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % (g))
 878             if info and remove_existing and self.group_info(g)[2] == info[3]:
 879                 groups.remove(g)
 880         return groups

 882     def user_group_membership(self, exclude_primary=True):
 883         ''' Return a list of groups the user belongs to '''
 884         groups = []
 885         info = self.get_pwd_info()
 886         for group in grp.getgrall():
 887             if self.name in group.gr_mem:
 888                 # Exclude the user's primary group by default
 889                 if not exclude_primary:
 890                     groups.append(group[0])
 891                 else:
 892                     if info[3] != group.gr_gid:
 893                         groups.append(group[0])
 894 
 895         return groups

 897     def user_exists(self):
 898         # The pwd module does not distinguish between local and directory accounts.
 899         # It's output cannot be used to determine whether or not an account exists locally.
 900         # It returns True if the account exists locally or in the directory, so instead
 901         # look in the local PASSWORD file for an existing account.
 902         if self.local:
 903             if not os.path.exists(self.PASSWORDFILE):
 904                 self.module.fail_json(msg="'local: true' specified but unable to find local account file {0} to parse.".format(self.PASSWORDFILE))
 905 
 906             exists = False
 907             name_test = '{0}:'.format(self.name)
 908             with open(self.PASSWORDFILE, 'rb') as f:
 909                 reversed_lines = f.readlines()[::-1]
 910                 for line in reversed_lines:
 911                     if line.startswith(to_bytes(name_test)):
 912                         exists = True
 913                         break
 914 
 915             if not exists:
 916                 self.module.warn(
 917                     "'local: true' specified and user '{name}' was not found in {file}. "
 918                     "The local user account may already exist if the local account database exists "
 919                     "somewhere other than {file}.".format(file=self.PASSWORDFILE, name=self.name))
 920 
 921             return exists
 922 
 923         else:
 924             try:
 925                 if pwd.getpwnam(self.name):
 926                     return True
 927             except KeyError:
 928                 return False
 929 
 930     def get_pwd_info(self):
 931         if not self.user_exists():
 932             return False
 933         return list(pwd.getpwnam(self.name))
 934 
 935     def user_info(self):
 936         if not self.user_exists():
 937             return False
 938         info = self.get_pwd_info()
 939         if len(info[1]) == 1 or len(info[1]) == 0:
 940             info[1] = self.user_password()[0]
 941         return info

 943     def user_password(self):
 944         passwd = ''
 945         expires = ''
 946         if HAVE_SPWD:
 947             try:
 948                 passwd = spwd.getspnam(self.name)[1]
 949                 expires = spwd.getspnam(self.name)[7]
 950                 return passwd, expires
 951             except KeyError:
 952                 return passwd, expires
 953             except OSError as e:
 954                 # Python 3.6 raises PermissionError instead of KeyError
 955                 # Due to absence of PermissionError in python2.7 need to check
 956                 # errno
 957                 if e.errno in (errno.EACCES, errno.EPERM, errno.ENOENT):
 958                     return passwd, expires
 959                 raise
 960 
 961         if not self.user_exists():
 962             return passwd, expires
 963         elif self.SHADOWFILE:
 964             passwd, expires = self.parse_shadow_file()
 965 
 966         return passwd, expires
 967 
 968     def parse_shadow_file(self):
 969         passwd = ''
 970         expires = ''
 971         if os.path.exists(self.SHADOWFILE) and os.access(self.SHADOWFILE, os.R_OK):
 972             with open(self.SHADOWFILE, 'r') as f:
 973                 for line in f:
 974                     if line.startswith('%s:' % self.name):
 975                         passwd = line.split(':')[1]
 976                         expires = line.split(':')[self.SHADOWFILE_EXPIRE_INDEX] or -1
 977         return passwd, expires

 979     def get_ssh_key_path(self):
 980         info = self.user_info()
 981         if os.path.isabs(self.ssh_file):
 982             ssh_key_file = self.ssh_file
 983         else:
 984             if not os.path.exists(info[5]) and not self.module.check_mode:
 985                 raise Exception('User %s home directory does not exist' % self.name)
 986             ssh_key_file = os.path.join(info[5], self.ssh_file)
 987         return ssh_key_file

 989     def ssh_key_gen(self):
 990         info = self.user_info()
 991         overwrite = None
 992         try:
 993             ssh_key_file = self.get_ssh_key_path()
 994         except Exception as e:
 995             return (1, '', to_native(e))
 996         ssh_dir = os.path.dirname(ssh_key_file)
 997         if not os.path.exists(ssh_dir):
 998             if self.module.check_mode:
 999                 return (0, '', '')
1000             try:
1001                 os.mkdir(ssh_dir, int('0700', 8))
1002                 os.chown(ssh_dir, info[2], info[3])
1003             except OSError as e:
1004                 return (1, '', 'Failed to create %s: %s' % (ssh_dir, to_native(e)))
1005         if os.path.exists(ssh_key_file):
1006             if self.force:
1007                 # ssh-keygen doesn't support overwriting the key interactively, so send 'y' to confirm
1008                 overwrite = 'y'
1009             else:
1010                 return (None, 'Key already exists, use "force: yes" to overwrite', '')
1011         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path('ssh-keygen', True)]
1012         cmd.append('-t')
1013         cmd.append(self.ssh_type)
1014         if self.ssh_bits > 0:
1015             cmd.append('-b')
1016             cmd.append(self.ssh_bits)
1017         cmd.append('-C')
1018         cmd.append(self.ssh_comment)
1019         cmd.append('-f')
1020         cmd.append(ssh_key_file)
1021         if self.ssh_passphrase is not None:
1022             if self.module.check_mode:
1023                 self.module.debug('In check mode, would have run: "%s"' % cmd)
1024                 return (0, '', '')
1025 
1026             master_in_fd, slave_in_fd = pty.openpty()
1027             master_out_fd, slave_out_fd = pty.openpty()
1028             master_err_fd, slave_err_fd = pty.openpty()
1029             env = os.environ.copy()
1030             env['LC_ALL'] = 'C'
1031             try:
1032                 p = subprocess.Popen([to_bytes(c) for c in cmd],
1033                                      stdin=slave_in_fd,
1034                                      stdout=slave_out_fd,
1035                                      stderr=slave_err_fd,
1036                                      preexec_fn=os.setsid,
1037                                      env=env)
1038                 out_buffer = b''
1039                 err_buffer = b''
1040                 while p.poll() is None:
1041                     r, w, e = select.select([master_out_fd, master_err_fd], [], [], 1)
1042                     first_prompt = b'Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase):'
1043                     second_prompt = b'Enter same passphrase again'
1044                     prompt = first_prompt
1045                     for fd in r:
1046                         if fd == master_out_fd:
1047                             chunk = os.read(master_out_fd, 10240)
1048                             out_buffer += chunk
1049                             if prompt in out_buffer:
1050                                 os.write(master_in_fd, to_bytes(self.ssh_passphrase, errors='strict') + b'\r')
1051                                 prompt = second_prompt
1052                         else:
1053                             chunk = os.read(master_err_fd, 10240)
1054                             err_buffer += chunk
1055                             if prompt in err_buffer:
1056                                 os.write(master_in_fd, to_bytes(self.ssh_passphrase, errors='strict') + b'\r')
1057                                 prompt = second_prompt
1058                         if b'Overwrite (y/n)?' in out_buffer or b'Overwrite (y/n)?' in err_buffer:
1059                             # The key was created between us checking for existence and now
1060                             return (None, 'Key already exists', '')
1061 
1062                 rc = p.returncode
1063                 out = to_native(out_buffer)
1064                 err = to_native(err_buffer)
1065             except OSError as e:
1066                 return (1, '', to_native(e))
1067         else:
1068             cmd.append('-N')
1069             cmd.append('')
1070 
1071             (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd, data=overwrite)
1072 
1073         if rc == 0 and not self.module.check_mode:
1074             # If the keys were successfully created, we should be able
1075             # to tweak ownership.
1076             os.chown(ssh_key_file, info[2], info[3])
1077             os.chown('%s.pub' % ssh_key_file, info[2], info[3])
1078         return (rc, out, err)
1079 
1080     def ssh_key_fingerprint(self):

1085         cmd.append('-l')
1086         cmd.append('-f')
1087         cmd.append(ssh_key_file)
1088 
1089         return self.execute_command(cmd, obey_checkmode=False)

1112     def create_homedir(self, path):
1113         if not os.path.exists(path):
1114             if self.skeleton is not None:
1115                 skeleton = self.skeleton
1116             else:
1117                 skeleton = '/etc/skel'
1118 
1119             if os.path.exists(skeleton):
1120                 try:
1121                     shutil.copytree(skeleton, path, symlinks=True)
1122                 except OSError as e:
1123                     self.module.exit_json(failed=True, msg="%s" % to_native(e))
1124             else:
1125                 try:
1126                     os.makedirs(path)
1127                 except OSError as e:
1128                     self.module.exit_json(failed=True, msg="%s" % to_native(e))
1129             # get umask from /etc/login.defs and set correct home mode
1130             if os.path.exists(self.LOGIN_DEFS):
1131                 with open(self.LOGIN_DEFS, 'r') as f:
1132                     for line in f:
1133                         m = re.match(r'^UMASK\s+(\d+)$', line)
1134                         if m:
1135                             umask = int(m.group(1), 8)
1136                             mode = 0o777 & ~umask
1137                             try:
1138                                 os.chmod(path, mode)
1139                             except OSError as e:
1140                                 self.module.exit_json(failed=True, msg="%s" % to_native(e))
1141 
1142     def chown_homedir(self, uid, gid, path):
1143         try:
1144             os.chown(path, uid, gid)
1145             for root, dirs, files in os.walk(path):
1146                 for d in dirs:
1147                     os.chown(os.path.join(root, d), uid, gid)
1148                 for f in files:
1149                     os.chown(os.path.join(root, f), uid, gid)
1150         except OSError as e:
1151             self.module.exit_json(failed=True, msg="%s" % to_native(e))

1156 class FreeBsdUser(User):
1157     """
1158     This is a FreeBSD User manipulation class - it uses the pw command
1159     to manipulate the user database, followed by the chpass command
1160     to change the password.
1161 
1162     This overrides the following methods from the generic class:-
1163       - create_user()
1164       - remove_user()
1165       - modify_user()
1166     """
1167 
1168     platform = 'FreeBSD'
1169     distribution = None
1170     SHADOWFILE = '/etc/master.passwd'

1199                 cmd.append('-o')

1211                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % self.group)
1212             cmd.append('-g')

1238                 cmd.append('0')
1239             else:
1240                 cmd.append(str(calendar.timegm(self.expires)))
1241 
1242         # system cannot be handled currently - should we error if its requested?
1243         # create the user
1244         (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)

1260     def modify_user(self):
1261         cmd = [
1262             self.module.get_bin_path('pw', True),
1263             'usermod',
1264             '-n',
1265             self.name
1266         ]
1267         cmd_len = len(cmd)
1268         info = self.user_info()
1269 
1270         if self.uid is not None and info[2] != int(self.uid):
1271             cmd.append('-u')
1272             cmd.append(self.uid)
1273 
1274             if self.non_unique:
1275                 cmd.append('-o')
1276 
1277         if self.comment is not None and info[4] != self.comment:
1278             cmd.append('-c')
1279             cmd.append(self.comment)
1280 
1281         if self.home is not None:
1282             if (info[5] != self.home and self.move_home) or (not os.path.exists(self.home) and self.create_home):
1283                 cmd.append('-m')
1284             if info[5] != self.home:
1285                 cmd.append('-d')
1286                 cmd.append(self.home)
1287 
1288             if self.skeleton is not None:
1289                 cmd.append('-k')
1290                 cmd.append(self.skeleton)
1291 
1292         if self.group is not None:
1293             if not self.group_exists(self.group):
1294                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % self.group)
1295             ginfo = self.group_info(self.group)
1296             if info[3] != ginfo[2]:
1297                 cmd.append('-g')
1298                 cmd.append(self.group)
1299 
1300         if self.shell is not None and info[6] != self.shell:
1301             cmd.append('-s')
1302             cmd.append(self.shell)
1303 
1304         if self.login_class is not None:
1305             # find current login class
1306             user_login_class = None
1307             if os.path.exists(self.SHADOWFILE) and os.access(self.SHADOWFILE, os.R_OK):
1308                 with open(self.SHADOWFILE, 'r') as f:
1309                     for line in f:
1310                         if line.startswith('%s:' % self.name):
1311                             user_login_class = line.split(':')[4]
1312 
1313             # act only if login_class change
1314             if self.login_class != user_login_class:
1315                 cmd.append('-L')
1316                 cmd.append(self.login_class)
1317 
1318         if self.groups is not None:
1319             current_groups = self.user_group_membership()
1320             groups = self.get_groups_set()
1321 
1322             group_diff = set(current_groups).symmetric_difference(groups)
1323             groups_need_mod = False
1324 
1325             if group_diff:
1326                 if self.append:
1327                     for g in groups:
1328                         if g in group_diff:
1329                             groups_need_mod = True
1330                             break
1331                 else:
1332                     groups_need_mod = True
1333 
1334             if groups_need_mod:
1335                 cmd.append('-G')
1336                 new_groups = groups
1337                 if self.append:
1338                     new_groups = groups | set(current_groups)
1339                 cmd.append(','.join(new_groups))
1340 
1341         if self.expires is not None:
1342 
1343             current_expires = int(self.user_password()[1])
1344 
1345             # If expiration is negative or zero and the current expiration is greater than zero, disable expiration.
1346             # In OpenBSD, setting expiration to zero disables expiration. It does not expire the account.
1347             if self.expires <= time.gmtime(0):
1348                 if current_expires > 0:
1349                     cmd.append('-e')
1350                     cmd.append('0')
1351             else:
1352                 # Convert days since Epoch to seconds since Epoch as struct_time
1353                 current_expire_date = time.gmtime(current_expires)
1354 
1355                 # Current expires is negative or we compare year, month, and day only
1356                 if current_expires <= 0 or current_expire_date[:3] != self.expires[:3]:
1357                     cmd.append('-e')
1358                     cmd.append(str(calendar.timegm(self.expires)))
1359 
1360         # modify the user if cmd will do anything
1361         if cmd_len != len(cmd):
1362             (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)
1363             if rc is not None and rc != 0:
1364                 self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
1365         else:
1366             (rc, out, err) = (None, '', '')
1367 
1368         # we have to set the password in a second command
1369         if self.update_password == 'always' and self.password is not None and info[1] != self.password:
1370             cmd = [
1371                 self.module.get_bin_path('chpass', True),
1372                 '-p',
1373                 self.password,
1374                 self.name
1375             ]
1376             return self.execute_command(cmd)
1377 
1378         # we have to lock/unlock the password in a distinct command
1379         if self.password_lock and not info[1].startswith('*LOCKED*'):
1380             cmd = [
1381                 self.module.get_bin_path('pw', True),
1382                 'lock',
1383                 self.name
1384             ]
1385             if self.uid is not None and info[2] != int(self.uid):
1386                 cmd.append('-u')
1387                 cmd.append(self.uid)
1388             return self.execute_command(cmd)
1389         elif self.password_lock is False and info[1].startswith('*LOCKED*'):
1390             cmd = [
1391                 self.module.get_bin_path('pw', True),
1392                 'unlock',
1393                 self.name
1394             ]
1395             if self.uid is not None and info[2] != int(self.uid):
1396                 cmd.append('-u')
1397                 cmd.append(self.uid)
1398             return self.execute_command(cmd)
1399         return (rc, out, err)

1743 class SunOS(User):
1744     """
1745     This is a SunOS User manipulation class - The main difference between
1746     this class and the generic user class is that Solaris-type distros
1747     don't support the concept of a "system" account and we need to
1748     edit the /etc/shadow file manually to set a password. (Ugh)
1749 
1750     This overrides the following methods from the generic class:-
1751       - create_user()
1752       - remove_user()
1753       - modify_user()
1754       - user_info()
1755     """
1756 
1757     platform = 'SunOS'
1758     distribution = None
1759     SHADOWFILE = '/etc/shadow'

1762     def get_password_defaults(self):
1763         # Read password aging defaults
1764         try:
1765             minweeks = ''
1766             maxweeks = ''
1767             warnweeks = ''
1768             with open("/etc/default/passwd", 'r') as f:
1769                 for line in f:
1770                     line = line.strip()
1771                     if (line.startswith('#') or line == ''):
1772                         continue
1773                     m = re.match(r'^([^#]*)#(.*)$', line)
1774                     if m:  # The line contains a hash / comment
1775                         line = m.group(1)
1776                     key, value = line.split('=')
1777                     if key == "MINWEEKS":
1778                         minweeks = value.rstrip('\n')
1779                     elif key == "MAXWEEKS":
1780                         maxweeks = value.rstrip('\n')
1781                     elif key == "WARNWEEKS":
1782                         warnweeks = value.rstrip('\n')
1783         except Exception as err:
1784             self.module.fail_json(msg="failed to read /etc/default/passwd: %s" % to_native(err))
1785 
1786         return (minweeks, maxweeks, warnweeks)

1856             if self.password is not None:
1857                 self.backup_shadow()

1859                 try:

1873                                 except ValueError:

1875                                     pass
1876                             if maxweeks:

1881                                     pass

1883                                 try:
1884                                     fields[5] = str(int(warnweeks) * 7)
1885                                 except ValueError:
1886                                     # mirror solaris, which allows for any value in this field, and ignores anything that is not an int.
1887                                     pass
1888                             line = ':'.join(fields)
1889                             lines.append('%s\n' % line)
1890                     with open(self.SHADOWFILE, 'w+') as f:
1891                         f.writelines(lines)
1892                 except Exception as err:
1893                     self.module.fail_json(msg="failed to update users password: %s" % to_native(err))

1897     def modify_user_usermod(self):
1898         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path('usermod', True)]
1899         cmd_len = len(cmd)

1962             cmd.append('-R')

1970                 self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
1971         else:
1972             (rc, out, err) = (None, '', '')

2013     def _user_attr_info(self):
2014         info = [''] * 3
2015         with open(self.USER_ATTR, 'r') as file_handler:
2016             for line in file_handler:

2019                     tmp = dict(x.split('=') for x in lines[1].split(';'))
2020                     info[0] = tmp.get('profiles', '')
2021                     info[1] = tmp.get('auths', '')
2022                     info[2] = tmp.get('roles', '')

2089     def _get_user_property(self, property):

2112     def _get_next_uid(self, system=None):
2113         '''
2114         Return the next available uid. If system=True, then
2115         uid should be below of 500, if possible.
2116         '''
2117         cmd = self._get_dscl()
2118         cmd += ['-list', '/Users', 'UniqueID']
2119         (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd, obey_checkmode=False)
2120         if rc != 0:
2121             self.module.fail_json(
2122                 msg="Unable to get the next available uid",
2123                 rc=rc,
2124                 out=out,
2125                 err=err
2126             )
2127 
2128         max_uid = 0
2129         max_system_uid = 0
2130         for line in out.splitlines():
2131             current_uid = int(line.split(' ')[-1])
2132             if max_uid < current_uid:
2133                 max_uid = current_uid
2134             if max_system_uid < current_uid and current_uid < 500:
2135                 max_system_uid = current_uid
2136 
2137         if system and (0 < max_system_uid < 499):
2138             return max_system_uid + 1
2139         return max_uid + 1

2141     def _change_user_password(self):
2142         '''Change password for SELF.NAME against SELF.PASSWORD.
2143 
2144         Please note that password must be cleartext.
2145         '''
2146         # some documentation on how is stored passwords on OSX:
2147         # http://blog.lostpassword.com/2012/07/cracking-mac-os-x-lion-accounts-passwords/
2148         # http://null-byte.wonderhowto.com/how-to/hack-mac-os-x-lion-passwords-0130036/
2149         # http://pastebin.com/RYqxi7Ca
2150         # on OSX 10.8+ hash is SALTED-SHA512-PBKDF2
2151         # https://pythonhosted.org/passlib/lib/passlib.hash.pbkdf2_digest.html
2152         # https://gist.github.com/nueh/8252572
2153         cmd = self._get_dscl()
2154         if self.password:
2155             cmd += ['-passwd', '/Users/%s' % self.name, self.password]
2156         else:
2157             cmd += ['-create', '/Users/%s' % self.name, 'Password', '*']
2158         (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)
2159         if rc != 0:
2160             self.module.fail_json(msg='Error when changing password', err=err, out=out, rc=rc)
2161         return (rc, out, err)

2188     def _modify_group(self):
2189         '''Add or remove SELF.NAME to or from GROUP depending on ACTION.
2190         ACTION can be 'add' or 'remove' otherwise 'remove' is assumed. '''
2191 
2192         rc = 0
2193         out = ''
2194         err = ''
2195         changed = False
2196 
2197         current = set(self._list_user_groups())
2198         if self.groups is not None:
2199             target = set(self.groups.split(','))
2200         else:

2220     def _update_system_user(self):
2221         '''Hide or show user on login window according SELF.SYSTEM.
2222 
2223         Returns 0 if a change has been made, None otherwise.'''
2224 
2225         plist_file = '/Library/Preferences/com.apple.loginwindow.plist'
2226 
2227         # http://support.apple.com/kb/HT5017?viewlocale=en_US
2228         cmd = ['defaults', 'read', plist_file, 'HiddenUsersList']
2229         (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd, obey_checkmode=False)
2230         # returned value is
2231         # (
2232         #   "_userA",
2233         #   "_UserB",
2234         #   userc
2235         # )
2236         hidden_users = []
2237         for x in out.splitlines()[1:-1]:
2238             try:
2239                 x = x.split('"')[1]
2240             except IndexError:
2241                 x = x.strip()
2242             hidden_users.append(x)
2243 
2244         if self.system:
2245             if self.name not in hidden_users:
2246                 cmd = ['defaults', 'write', plist_file, 'HiddenUsersList', '-array-add', self.name]
2247                 (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)
2248                 if rc != 0:
2249                     self.module.fail_json(msg='Cannot user "%s" to hidden user list.' % self.name, err=err, out=out, rc=rc)
2250                 return 0
2251         else:
2252             if self.name in hidden_users:
2253                 del (hidden_users[hidden_users.index(self.name)])
2254 
2255                 cmd = ['defaults', 'write', plist_file, 'HiddenUsersList', '-array'] + hidden_users
2256                 (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)
2257                 if rc != 0:
2258                     self.module.fail_json(msg='Cannot remove user "%s" from hidden user list.' % self.name, err=err, out=out, rc=rc)

2286     def create_user(self, command_name='dscl'):

2302                 if not os.path.exists(self.home):
2303                     os.makedirs(self.home)

2319 
2320                 out += _out
2321                 err += _err
2322                 if rc != 0:
2323                     return (rc, _err, _out)
2324 
2325         (rc, _err, _out) = self._change_user_password()
2326         out += _out
2327         err += _err
2328 
2329         self._update_system_user()

2331         # thus changed is always true.

2338     def modify_user(self):
2339         changed = None

2358                     out += _out
2359                     err += _err

2362             out += _out
2363             err += _err
2364             changed = rc

2459             cmd.append('-u')
2460             cmd.append(self.uid)
2461 
2462         if self.group is not None:
2463             if not self.group_exists(self.group):
2464                 self.module.fail_json(msg="Group %s does not exist" % self.group)
2465             ginfo = self.group_info(self.group)
2466             if info[3] != ginfo[2]:
2467                 cmd.append('-g')
2468                 cmd.append(self.group)
2469 
2470         if self.groups is not None:
2471             current_groups = self.user_group_membership()
2472             groups_need_mod = False
2473             groups = []
2474 
2475             if self.groups == '':
2476                 if current_groups and not self.append:
2477                     groups_need_mod = True
2478             else:
2479                 groups = self.get_groups_set()
2480                 group_diff = set(current_groups).symmetric_difference(groups)
2481 
2482                 if group_diff:
2483                     if self.append:
2484                         for g in groups:
2485                             if g in group_diff:
2486                                 groups_need_mod = True
2487                                 break
2488                     else:
2489                         groups_need_mod = True
2490 
2491             if groups_need_mod:
2492                 cmd.append('-G')
2493                 cmd.append(','.join(groups))
2494 
2495         if self.comment is not None and info[4] != self.comment:
2496             cmd.append('-c')
2497             cmd.append(self.comment)
2498 
2499         if self.home is not None and info[5] != self.home:
2500             if self.move_home:
2501                 cmd.append('-m')
2502             cmd.append('-d')
2503             cmd.append(self.home)
2504 
2505         if self.shell is not None and info[6] != self.shell:
2506             cmd.append('-s')
2507             cmd.append(self.shell)
2508 
2509         # skip if no changes to be made
2510         if len(cmd) == 1:
2511             (rc, out, err) = (None, '', '')
2512         else:
2513             cmd.append(self.name)
2514             (rc, out, err) = self.execute_command(cmd)
2515 
2516         # set password with chpasswd
2517         if self.update_password == 'always' and self.password is not None and info[1] != self.password:
2518             cmd = []
2519             cmd.append(self.module.get_bin_path('chpasswd', True))
2520             cmd.append('-e')
2521             cmd.append('-c')
2522             (rc2, out2, err2) = self.execute_command(cmd, data="%s:%s" % (self.name, self.password))
2523         else:
2524             (rc2, out2, err2) = (None, '', '')
2525 
2526         if rc is not None:
2527             return (rc, out + out2, err + err2)
2528         else:
2529             return (rc2, out + out2, err + err2)

2531     def parse_shadow_file(self):
2532         """Example AIX shadowfile data:
2533         nobody:
2534                 password = *
2535 
2536         operator1:
2537                 password = {ssha512}06$xxxxxxxxxxxx....
2538                 lastupdate = 1549558094
2539 
2540         test1:
2541                 password = *
2542                 lastupdate = 1553695126
2543 
2544         """
2545 
2546         b_name = to_bytes(self.name)
2547         b_passwd = b''
2548         b_expires = b''
2549         if os.path.exists(self.SHADOWFILE) and os.access(self.SHADOWFILE, os.R_OK):
2550             with open(self.SHADOWFILE, 'rb') as bf:
2551                 b_lines = bf.readlines()
2552 
2553             b_passwd_line = b''
2554             b_expires_line = b''
2555             try:
2556                 for index, b_line in enumerate(b_lines):
2557                     # Get password and lastupdate lines which come after the username
2558                     if b_line.startswith(b'%s:' % b_name):
2559                         b_passwd_line = b_lines[index + 1]
2560                         b_expires_line = b_lines[index + 2]
2561                         break
2562 
2563                 # Sanity check the lines because sometimes both are not present
2564                 if b' = ' in b_passwd_line:
2565                     b_passwd = b_passwd_line.split(b' = ', 1)[-1].strip()
2566 
2567                 if b' = ' in b_expires_line:
2568                     b_expires = b_expires_line.split(b' = ', 1)[-1].strip()
2569 
2570             except IndexError:
2571                 self.module.fail_json(msg='Failed to parse shadow file %s' % self.SHADOWFILE)
2572 
2573         passwd = to_native(b_passwd)
2574         expires = to_native(b_expires) or -1
2575         return passwd, expires

2649     def modify_user(self):
2650         cmd = ['/usr/sam/lbin/usermod.sam']

2692                 if self.append:

2723 class BusyBox(User):
2724     """
2725     This is the BusyBox class for use on systems that have adduser, deluser,
2726     and delgroup commands. It overrides the following methods:
2727         - create_user()
2728         - remove_user()
2729         - modify_user()
2730     """
2731 
2732     def create_user(self):
2733         cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path('adduser', True)]
2734 
2735         cmd.append('-D')
2736 
2737         if self.uid is not None:
2738             cmd.append('-u')
2739             cmd.append(self.uid)
2740 
2741         if self.group is not None:
2742             if not self.group_exists(self.group):
2743                 self.module.fail_json(msg='Group {0} does not exist'.format(self.group))
2744             cmd.append('-G')
2745             cmd.append(self.group)
2746 
2747         if self.comment is not None:
2748             cmd.append('-g')
2749             cmd.append(self.comment)
2750 
2751         if self.home is not None:
2752             cmd.append('-h')
2753             cmd.append(self.home)
2754 
2755         if self.shell is not None:
2756             cmd.append('-s')
2757             cmd.append(self.shell)
2758 
2759         if not self.create_home:
2760             cmd.append('-H')
2761 
2762         if self.skeleton is not None:
2763             cmd.append('-k')
2764             cmd.append(self.skeleton)
2765 
2766         if self.system:
2767             cmd.append('-S')
2768 
2769         cmd.append(self.name)
2770 
2771         rc, out, err = self.execute_command(cmd)
2772 
2773         if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2774             self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2775 
2776         if self.password is not None:
2777             cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path('chpasswd', True)]
2778             cmd.append('--encrypted')
2779             data = '{name}:{password}'.format(name=self.name, password=self.password)
2780             rc, out, err = self.execute_command(cmd, data=data)
2781 
2782             if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2783                 self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2784 
2785         # Add to additional groups
2786         if self.groups is not None and len(self.groups):
2787             groups = self.get_groups_set()
2788             add_cmd_bin = self.module.get_bin_path('adduser', True)
2789             for group in groups:
2790                 cmd = [add_cmd_bin, self.name, group]
2791                 rc, out, err = self.execute_command(cmd)
2792                 if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2793                     self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2794 
2795         return rc, out, err
2796 
2797     def remove_user(self):
2798 
2799         cmd = [
2800             self.module.get_bin_path('deluser', True),
2801             self.name
2802         ]
2803 
2804         if self.remove:
2805             cmd.append('--remove-home')
2806 
2807         return self.execute_command(cmd)
2808 
2809     def modify_user(self):
2810         current_groups = self.user_group_membership()
2811         groups = []
2812         rc = None
2813         out = ''
2814         err = ''
2815         info = self.user_info()
2816         add_cmd_bin = self.module.get_bin_path('adduser', True)
2817         remove_cmd_bin = self.module.get_bin_path('delgroup', True)
2818 
2819         # Manage group membership
2820         if self.groups is not None and len(self.groups):
2821             groups = self.get_groups_set()
2822             group_diff = set(current_groups).symmetric_difference(groups)
2823 
2824             if group_diff:
2825                 for g in groups:
2826                     if g in group_diff:
2827                         add_cmd = [add_cmd_bin, self.name, g]
2828                         rc, out, err = self.execute_command(add_cmd)
2829                         if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2830                             self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2831 
2832                 for g in group_diff:
2833                     if g not in groups and not self.append:
2834                         remove_cmd = [remove_cmd_bin, self.name, g]
2835                         rc, out, err = self.execute_command(remove_cmd)
2836                         if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2837                             self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2838 
2839         # Manage password
2840         if self.update_password == 'always' and self.password is not None and info[1] != self.password:
2841             cmd = [self.module.get_bin_path('chpasswd', True)]
2842             cmd.append('--encrypted')
2843             data = '{name}:{password}'.format(name=self.name, password=self.password)
2844             rc, out, err = self.execute_command(cmd, data=data)
2845 
2846             if rc is not None and rc != 0:
2847                 self.module.fail_json(name=self.name, msg=err, rc=rc)
2848 
2849         return rc, out, err
